#. type: Yaml Front Matter Hash Value: title
#: docs/admin/45.tutorials/60.security.mdx:1
#, no-wrap
msgid "Security"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: docs/admin/45.tutorials/60.security.mdx:6
msgid ""
"YunoHost has been developed to provide the best security without too much "
"complication. Every protocol used in YunoHost is **encrypted**, only a "
"password's hashes are stored and by default each user is able to access "
"their personal directory only."
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: docs/admin/45.tutorials/60.security.mdx:8
msgid "Two things remain important to note:"
msgstr ""

#. type: Bullet: '- '
#: docs/admin/45.tutorials/60.security.mdx:10
msgid ""
"Installing additional apps can **significantly increase** the number of "
"potential security flaws. Do not hesitate to get information about security "
"flaws **before installing an app**, and try to only install apps which will "
"suit your needs."
msgstr ""

#. type: Bullet: '- '
#: docs/admin/45.tutorials/60.security.mdx:12
msgid ""
"The fact that YunoHost is a well-known and used piece of software increases "
"the chances of an attack. If a flaw is discovered, it could potentially "
"affect all YunoHost instances at once. Keep your system **up-to-date** to "
"remain safe. Updates can be automated by installing the "
"[\"Unattended_upgrades\" app](https://install-app.yunohost.org/?"
"app=unattended_upgrades)."
msgstr ""

#. type: Fenced div block (tip)
#: docs/admin/45.tutorials/60.security.mdx:13
#, no-wrap
msgid "If you need advice, do not hesitate to [ask us](/community/help).\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Fenced div block (danger)
#: docs/admin/45.tutorials/60.security.mdx:17
#, no-wrap
msgid "<FAIcon icon=\"fa-shield\"/> To discuss security flaws, contact the [YunoHost security team](/community/security_team).\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Title ##
#: docs/admin/45.tutorials/60.security.mdx:23
#, no-wrap
msgid "Improve security"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: docs/admin/45.tutorials/60.security.mdx:26
msgid ""
"If your YunoHost server is used in a critical production environment, or if "
"you want to improve its safety, you may want to follow these good practices."
msgstr ""

#. type: Fenced div block (warning)
#: docs/admin/45.tutorials/60.security.mdx:27
#, no-wrap
msgid "Following these instructions requires advanced knowledge of system administration.\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Fenced div block (tip)
#: docs/admin/45.tutorials/60.security.mdx:31
#, no-wrap
msgid "Never close your current SSH connection before checking that your alterations work. Test your new configuration by opening a new terminal or window. That way, you can undo your alterations if anything goes wrong.\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Title ###
#: docs/admin/45.tutorials/60.security.mdx:35
#, no-wrap
msgid "SSH authentication via key"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: docs/admin/45.tutorials/60.security.mdx:38
msgid ""
"By default, the SSH authentication uses the administration password. "
"Deactivating this kind of authentication and replacing it by a key mechanism "
"is advised."
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: docs/admin/45.tutorials/60.security.mdx:40
#, no-wrap
msgid "**On your client**:\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Fenced code block (bash)
#: docs/admin/45.tutorials/60.security.mdx:41
#, no-wrap
msgid ""
"ssh-keygen\n"
"ssh-copy-id -i ~/.ssh/id_rsa.pub <username@your_yunohost_server>\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Fenced div block (tip)
#: docs/admin/45.tutorials/60.security.mdx:46
#, no-wrap
msgid ""
"If you run into permissions issues, set `username` as owner of the dir `~/.ssh` with `chown`. Be careful, for security reasons this directory should be in mode `700`.  \n"
"If you are on Ubuntu 16.04 you should run `ssh-add` to initialize the SSH agent.\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: docs/admin/45.tutorials/60.security.mdx:52
msgid ""
"Type your admnistration password and your key will be copied onto your "
"server."
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: docs/admin/45.tutorials/60.security.mdx:54
#, no-wrap
msgid "**On your server**, editing the SSH configuration file to deactivate password authentication is handled by a system setting:\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Fenced code block (bash)
#: docs/admin/45.tutorials/60.security.mdx:55
#, no-wrap
msgid "sudo yunohost settings set security.ssh.ssh_password_authentication -v no\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Title ###
#: docs/admin/45.tutorials/60.security.mdx:61
#, no-wrap
msgid "Modify the SSH port"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: docs/admin/45.tutorials/60.security.mdx:64
#, no-wrap
msgid ""
"To prevent SSH connection attempts by robots that scan the internet for any server with SSH enabled, you can change the SSH port.\n"
"This is handled by a system setting, which takes care of updating the SSH and Fail2Ban configuration.  \n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: docs/admin/45.tutorials/60.security.mdx:66
msgid ""
"There's no need to change this port if you've disabled password "
"authentication."
msgstr ""

#. type: Fenced div block (warning)
#: docs/admin/45.tutorials/60.security.mdx:67
#, no-wrap
msgid "If you modify anything in the `/etc/ssh/sshd_config` file, even if only the port, YunoHost will no longer manage this file. For this reason, always use the YunoHost admin tools to make changes to the systems configuration files!\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Fenced code block (bash)
#: docs/admin/45.tutorials/60.security.mdx:71
#, no-wrap
msgid "sudo yunohost settings set security.ssh.ssh_port -v <new_ssh_port_number>\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: docs/admin/45.tutorials/60.security.mdx:76
#, no-wrap
msgid "**For subsequent SSH connections**, you need to add the `-p` option followed by the SSH port number.\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: docs/admin/45.tutorials/60.security.mdx:78
#, no-wrap
msgid "**Sample**:\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Fenced code block (bash)
#: docs/admin/45.tutorials/60.security.mdx:79
#, no-wrap
msgid "ssh -p <new_ssh_port_number> admin@<your_yunohost_server>\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Title ###
#: docs/admin/45.tutorials/60.security.mdx:85
#, no-wrap
msgid "Change cipher compatibility configuration"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: docs/admin/45.tutorials/60.security.mdx:88
msgid ""
"The default TLS configuration for services tends to offer good compatibility "
"to support old devices. You can tune this policy for specific services like "
"SSH and NGINX. By default, the NGINX configuration follows the [intermediate "
"compatibility recommendation](https://wiki.mozilla.org/Security/"
"Server_Side_TLS#Intermediate_compatibility_.28default.29) from Mozilla. You "
"can choose to switch to the 'modern' configuration which uses more recent "
"security recommendations, but decreases compatibility, which may be an issue "
"for your users and visitors using older devices. More details about "
"compatibility can be found on [this page](https://wiki.mozilla.org/Security/"
"Server_Side_TLS#Modern_compatibility)."
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: docs/admin/45.tutorials/60.security.mdx:90
msgid ""
"Changing the compatibility level is not definitive and can be reverted if it "
"doesn't fit with your environment."
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: docs/admin/45.tutorials/60.security.mdx:92
#, no-wrap
msgid "**On your server**, change the policy for NGINX\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Fenced code block (bash)
#: docs/admin/45.tutorials/60.security.mdx:93
#, no-wrap
msgid "sudo yunohost settings set security.nginx.nginx_compatibility -v modern\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: docs/admin/45.tutorials/60.security.mdx:98
#, no-wrap
msgid "**On your server**, change the policy for SSH\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Fenced code block (bash)
#: docs/admin/45.tutorials/60.security.mdx:99
#, no-wrap
msgid "sudo yunohost settings set security.ssh.ssh_compatibility -v modern\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Title ###
#: docs/admin/45.tutorials/60.security.mdx:103
#, no-wrap
msgid "Disable the YunoHost API"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: docs/admin/45.tutorials/60.security.mdx:108
msgid ""
"YunoHost administration is accessible through an **HTTP API**, served on the "
"6787 port by default (only on `localhost`).  It can be used to administer a "
"lot of things on your server, so malicious actors can also use it to damage "
"your server.  The best thing to do, if you know how to use the [command-line "
"interface (CLI)](/admin/command_line), is to deactivate the `yunohost-api` "
"service."
msgstr ""

#. type: Fenced div block (warning)
#: docs/admin/45.tutorials/60.security.mdx:109
#, no-wrap
msgid ""
"This will completely disable both YunoHost's API and the web administration panel that relies on it.\n"
"Proceed only if you are comfortable with the command line interface.\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Fenced code block (bash)
#: docs/admin/45.tutorials/60.security.mdx:114
#, no-wrap
msgid ""
"sudo systemctl disable yunohost-api\n"
"sudo systemctl stop yunohost-api\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: docs/admin/45.tutorials/60.security.mdx:121
msgid ""
"As `yunohost-api` is now disabled and not running, Diagnosis will report an "
"error and cannot be ignored from the API.  If you want to ignore this error, "
"you can configure YunoHost from the CLI."
msgstr ""

#. type: Fenced code block (bash)
#: docs/admin/45.tutorials/60.security.mdx:122
#, no-wrap
msgid "sudo yunohost diagnosis ignore --filter services service=yunohost-api\n"
msgstr ""
